---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Agent Merge">
  <h1>Agent Merge</h1>
  <p>
    Once Copilot Code Review leaves its comments, Agent Merge is what actually closes the loop.
    It reads the review findings, pushes the fixes — pin the Action, scope the token, validate
    the input — and merges the pull request the moment checks go green.
  </p>
  <p>
    The same pattern handles routine hygiene: when Dependabot opens a version-bump PR for an
    outdated package, Agent Merge merges it automatically once the build and security checks
    pass. No one has to remember to click merge on a dependency bump ever again.
  </p>
  <div class="card">
    This is the headline capability in the live demo: an AI-written PR goes in with real issues,
    and comes out the other side fixed and merged, without a human doing the mechanical work.
  </div>
</Layout>
